detail.title: Change maximum block size from 21 MB to 1MB
detail.description:
## TL:DR: 
- following a reported security advise it is recommended to make the maximum allowed block size of the BitCanna chain smaller
- passing this proposal lowers the maximum allowed block size from 21 MB to 1 MB
- since we use 300kB for our biggest blocks, the new maximum allowed block size still leaves a lot of room for growth
## Description: 
In a reported security advise (Amulet Security Advisory ASA-2023-002 and based on research from Jacob Gadikian for whom is interested) it was advised to investigate the maximum block size a chain needs.

Why are we doing this? For this we need to look at what happened elsewhere in the ecosystem. Recently we have seen spam on for example Osmosis where bots are spamming large amounts of data on chain. This causes the chain to have difficulties handling all transactions and resulting in the inability for users to use the chain (Osmosis in this case).

One counter-measure is reducing the maximum allowed size of each block. In our current settings this is limited to 21 MB, but our data shows that we are using only a fraction of that (maximum of 300kB per block).

We propose to change the maximum allowed block size to 1 MB. This is still 3 times higher than our current observed maximum, allowing for room to grow; but small enough to be prepared for on chain spam.

Find more information about parameters for blocks here:
https://docs.cometbft.com/v0.34/spec/abci/apps#blockparamsmaxbytes

detail.title: Vote _wake and bake_ release - v2.0.2 to perform the Cosmos-SDK v0.46 ugprade
detail.description:
It is time for our chain to be upgraded to a newer version of the Cosmos SDK. We will migrate from v0.45.16 to v0.46.13. This is a state-breaking upgrade and will therefore need a governance proposal and a chain halt.

With this proposal we set a new upgrade height at block 9.209.420 (29-06-2023 around 15:15 CEST) with the codename _wakeandbake_ (v2.0.2). At the given height the chain will halt and all validators have to change the binary to the new version. After a brief downtime the chain will resume operations.

Upgrade height: 9209420 (https://www.mintscan.io/bitcanna/blocks/9209420)

What will be upgraded and implemented:
* Upgrade Cosmos-SDK from v0.45.16 to v0.46.13 & CometBFT v0.34.28
* Check and avoid duplicates at Bitcannaid.bcnaid
* New endpoint for BCNA module /BitCannaGlobal/bcna/bcna/bitcannaid/bcnaid/{bcnaid}
* Code refactor to deprecate Ignite OpenAPIConsole deps
* Refactor Gov Spam filter to reject v1 proposals, only v1beta1 are allowed for SDK v0.46
* Ante handler to prevent spam proposals at Gov module
* Bump IBC go version to v6.1.0 & IAVL version to v0.19.5
* Fixed BCNA module path & bug with CLI
* Added endpoint nodeconfig
* Upgrades separated from App.go
* Deprecate ignite/cli cosmoscmd package
* Refactor tests and root & delete comments

For more information about the upgrade's content:
* https://github.com/BitCannaGlobal/bcna/blob/main/last_upgrade.md#v202-codename-wakeandbake-from-v170

detail.title: Codename: Vigorous-Grow-Huckleberry - v1.7.0
detail.description:
# Upgrade Codename: Vigorous-Grow-Huckleberry - v1.7.0
**On Chain proposal:**
 What will be upgraded and implemented:
Huckleberry patch
-Upgrade from IBC v3.4.0 to IBC v4.4.1
- Upgrade Cosmos-SDK from v0.45.15 to v0.45.16
- Upgrade CometBFT from v0.34.27 to v0.34.28
**Description:** 
A safety patch has been released for IBC Go which is advised to apply as soon as possible. Where we intended to update our blockchain with the upcoming upgrade to Cosmos-SDK v0.46.x we will now do an upgrade to be able to apply the patch. For that reason the chain needs to be halted.

With this proposal we set a new upgrade height at block 8.771.420 (30-05-2023 around 15:45h CEST) with the codename vigorous-grow-huckleberry (v1.7.0). At the given height the chain will halt and all validators have to change the binary to the new version. After a brief downtime the chain will resume operations.

Upgrade height:[8771420](https://www.mintscan.io/bitcanna/blocks/8771420)

detail.title: Upgrade Codename: Vigorous-Grow-fix - v1.6.1
detail.description:
# Upgrade Codename: Vigorous-Grow-fix - v1.6.1
- Fix AntiSpam new feature at Gov Proposals


On 02-03-2023 at height 7.467.420 our chain was upgraded to v1.6.0 under the codename Vigorous Grow.
In the past few days a bug surfaced where transactions could be sent without consuming gas (see it like gasoline for your car or electricity for your mobile phone).
This caused problems for the validators securing our chain, since every transaction needs to consume gas, regardless of the fee paid for the gas consumed.

This bug makes it impossible for new nodes to synchronize to the chain, and also causes nodes to crash if they restart. Also we experimented some issues with failed TXs. This is not desired of course, which is why we created a fix. We coordinated with several parties to troubleshoot, thanks to the Cosmos SDK group, Notional and Informal Systems.

With this proposal we set a new upgrade height at block 7585420 (10-03-2023 around 18:40h CET) with the codename vigorous-grow-fix (v1.6.1). At the given height the chain will halt and all validators have to change the binary to the new version. After a brief downtime the chain will resume operations.

Upgrade height:
https://www.mintscan.io/bitcanna/blocks/7585420

detail.title: Burning Buddheads: Mayhem or gentle?
detail.description:
# **TL:DR:** following the outcome of proposal 5; this proposal is to determine how we are going to burn the Buddheads.
* Vote **Yes** if you want to burn all unsold Buddheads, all at the same time
* Vote **No** if you want to burn unsold Buddheads in smaller batches on a monthly basis
* If you don’t want to burn unsold Buddheads, you can vote **Abstain** on this proposal
## Vote **Ye** for: Burn them all! 
Proposal 5 has shown that we have a community which is an avid supporter of mayhem and destruction. If you are; vote **Yes** on this proposal you are in favor of getting rid of all remaining Buddheads in one go.
This would mean that the remaining 3000+ Buddheads are burned in one batch. We will create a script for that to accommodate the process. Since all Buddheads can be seen as minted in this case, the rarity score on [Hubble](https://www.hubble.tools/collections/bitcanna-buddheads) should become available.
Furthermore, the promised airdrop of 50% of the proceeds will be smaller, but immediately executable.
So, if you are in favor of burning the rest of the Buddhead collection in one batch, vote **Yes” on this proposal.
## Vote **No** for: Burn them all, but do it gently
We can also imagine you like destruction, but want it to last. Since June we started with our monthly updates. We can give each new edition a nice touch with a new set of burned NFTs. If you vote **No” on this proposal you are in favor of burning a batch of Buddheads at the time of each dev update.
This would mean that we will determine an amount (e.g. batches of 420 NFTs) which are burned at the time of the dev updates. We will create a script for that to accommodate the process. In each dev update we will give an overview of where we are in the process and an expected timeline with respect to the remaining batches to be burned.
Furthermore, the promised airdrop of 50% of the proceeds might grow compared to the situation as we have today, since in the meantime more NFTs can still be sold. With this scenario we can also determine the latest date on which the airdrop will occur as well as when the rarity score on [Hubble](https://www.hubble.tools/collections/bitcanna-buddheads) will be available latest.
So, if you are in favor of burning the rest of the Buddhead collection in batches together with the release of each new dev update, vote **No” on this proposal.

detail.title: To burn or not to burn, that is the question
detail.description:
## **TL:DR:** this proposal is to determine whether you want to burn Buddheads at all.
* Vote “Yes” on this proposal if you want to burn Buddheads. How to do this will be subject of another proposal which will be raised when the outcome of this proposal is known.
* Vote “No” if you don’t want to burn Buddheads
## Introduction
On 20-04-2022 we started with our [Buddhead NFT collection](https://app.stargaze.zone/launchpad/stars1cpzvvmlrc9lcw3q5yrznax0uk5h6xww2d4ch9xve4xu8mfvgw2kqepnwd2). Over 3000 NFTs were airdropped to holders of the BCNA-coin, providers of liquidity in one the BCNA pools on Osmosis and to holders of the STARS-coin. In hindsight we issued too many Buddheads. We anticipated on market conditions at the time, however, the global cryptocurrency market quickly tumbled simultaneously to our release schedule.

From these unminted NFTs we will mint a batch of 200 Buddheads to our marketing address for future purposes. This makes the total of NFTs to be used for marketing purposes 602 Buddheads. We would like to burn the remainder of the unminted supply of these Buddheads to better serve the community. And for that purpose we need your input. In two governance proposals we will define the path forward with the Buddheads together with you, the community.

In the end we will review the results and execute the proposal with the highest outcome in terms of votes. So it is important to vote, since you have direct influence on the outcome of the voting! Read the proposal carefully and cast your vote accordingly.

## Proposal: My precious, don’t burn them please
We can imagine that you love to see all the Buddheads come to life and are curious to see what kind of nice combination of attributes are still waiting to be minted. If you vote “**No**” on this proposal you are in favor of not burning any Buddhead at all.
This would mean that the minting on Stargaze will stay open until the last Buddhead has been minted. The rarity score on [Hubble](https://www.hubble.tools/collections/bitcanna-buddheads) will only show after the last Buddhead has been minted.

Furthermore, **the promised airdrop of 50%** of the proceeds also have to wait until that point in time. The airdrop will be bigger though, since more STARS are collected from the sale of the Buddheads.

So, if you are in favor of keeping the Buddhead collection complete without burning, vote “**No**” on this proposal.

If you are in favor of burning Buddheads, vote “**Yes**” on this proposal. How to do this will be subject of another proposal which will be raised when the outcome of this proposal is known.

detail.title: Vote strangeBuddheads version (v1.4.1) to get last update securities from Tendermint v0.34.20 & SDK Cosmos v.0.45.7 & IBC/go v.3.1.1
detail.description:
PROPOSAL: Vote **strangeBuddheads** version **(v1.4.1)** to get the latest security update from Tendermint v0.34.20 & SDK Cosmos v.0.45.7 & IBC/go v.3.1.1.

> Note: When using Cosmos SDK 0.45.7, the restart of the binary could **take up to 15 minutes** in order to build the fast cache of IAVL. The fast cache will provide a performance improvement over 0.45.1 (our current at Ruderalis).
 
Additionally, we are including the SDK ***authz*** module which introduces the ***Restake*** functionality and some other on-chain functionality such as **Grants**.

Also we have fixed the ***bcna*** module & we have added a new extra field for ***Supply Chain*** tracking.
